Description: Oval handle of a pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay medium red-brown. Circular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Eukratidas. Trimmed. Perhaps from same die as a piece from Kaunos, B.Schmaltz, Die Hellenistischen Amphorenstempel vom Kaunos (Asia Minor Studien 79) 94, KA 224. From same die as BM 1925,0119.429b and 430 and Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0919.05.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0378)
Acquisition date: 1886 (Surface preservation and trimming suggest that this is an acquisition from Petrie.)
